strategy were those related with HCC risk (HBV DNA levels, platelet counts and 
age) and drug cost.
CONCLUSION: Starting antiviral therapy in IT phase is cost-effective compared 
with delaying the treatment until the active hepatitis phase in CHB patients, 
especially with increasing HCC risk, decreasing drug costs and consideration of 
productivity loss.

