Chronic non-cancer pain (CNCP) involves one-third of the US population, and 
prescription opioids contribute to the opioid epidemic. The Centers for Disease 
Control and Prevention emphasizes maximizing non-opioid treatment, but many 
rural populations cannot access alternative therapies. Clinical and 
Translational Science Award hubs across four rural states performed a 
multi-site, single-arm intervention feasibility study testing methods and 
